Environmental

Max Radiation Level: 170

Radioactive Decay: 1.1

Radioresistance: 0

Role & Upgrade Notes

Assault identity: gains more Hull slots than other Escort roles; Advanced Maul adds +1 Hull slot (and minor energy/survivability bumps).

Designed to trade speed/turn for armor and sustained presence on objective.

Frame Traits & Design Intent

Largest of the three Escort frames; reinforced plating and high durability.

Best used as a frontline screen or station guard; pairs well with Command escorts that supply buffs/ECM.

Weaknesses: slowest handling among escorts; vulnerable to kiting and EW drain if isolated.

Implementation Checklist

Enforce slot family sizes (all Medium).

Apply Assault role rule (+Hull slots, +1 more when upgraded).

Verify boost drain vs recharge allows ~8–10 s of continuous boost with typical engine modules.

Validate TTK vs peers: Maul should outlast Scythe/Glaive in equal DPS trades but lose chase potential.

